Understanding of Bits :

- Bit wise AND (&)
1 & 1 = 1
1 & 0 = 0

6 & 7 = 6
0110 & 0111 = 0110 = 6

Bitwise OR (|)
1 | 1 = 1
1 | 0 = 1
0 | 0 = 0

6 | 7 = 7

Bitwise Not (~)
~1 = 0
~0 = 1

~6 = 7
int a = 6 (32 bits)
000.....0110
~(000....0110) = 111....1001 = -7 (-ve numbers are stored in 2's complement form)

Bitwise XOR (^)
1^1 = 0
1^0 = 1
0^0 = 0

6 ^ 7 = 1

Left shift :
int a = 8
a << 2

8 = 1000
8 << 2 = 100000 = 32

Right shift :
int a=8
a >> 2
8 = 1000
8 >> 2 = 000010 = 2